that singular moment you are you are your toe you are your finger you are your tongue yeah and then you bounce out of it okay and become the observer become the knower of this pain and that's when the anger comes up you start beating the door up or the person who just stood on your toe and that's that's that's you've now jumped out of being the body right the physical body into being an emotion

